props.synopsis: In Australia's biggest trauma hospital, doctors are seeing an increase in older patients suffering injuries from falls. They say it is only going to get worse.

image.altText: A smiling blonde woman turns to face the camera as she paints a picture of a woman on an easel.

props.synopsis: From mood swings and anxiety to full-blown psychosis, many women experience significant changes in their mental health in the years leading up to menopause, but experts say a holistic approach can be key to alleviating the symptoms.

image.altText: Back view of a women in silhouette, looking out of a window at green garden.

props.synopsis: Australians paint a stark picture of extreme measures taken to save money, telling a cost-of-living Senate inquiry they only leave the house for essentials, no longer see loved ones, and have become socially isolated.

title.children: No more weekend BBQs, family visits or going out. Why Australians are being forced to socially isolate

image.altText: Teenage girls drinking from a water bottle and sticking their tongue out

image.altText: A drone photo above the highway with bush burnt on either side and a car and caravan travelling through.

props.synopsis: After another bushfire closes the Eyre Highway, the Shire of Dundas says it needs more support to battle the massive fires in the Great Western Woodlands.

image.altText: Pope Francis raises his hand and holds a white book in front of him

title.children: Pope Francis urges Ukraine to have 'courage of the white flag' and negotiate end to war

image.altText: A young blonde woman sings and plays the guitar.

image.altText: A family of 8 stands in front of a large blue and white bus with three dogs and one cat.
